blueprint.description:
Connect the [item=green-wire] on the [item=substation] to the global network to enable reading of how many 1-1 trains worth of material this station has in it's buffers.
Add inserters, boxes, and a supply belt to the other side of the track (dont forget to wire the boxes together) to not only increase the buffer size, but also double the fill speed. 
With Boxes and bulk inserters on both sides, can fill a car in ~ 5 seconds.

Calculate by taking quantity of whatever is in the boxes, and dividing it by [virtual-signal=signal-K](The capacity of the train to hold that 'parameterized' item)

Add Stack inserters to potentially quadruple belt capacity.

3600 game ticks= 1 minute

Final values after parameterizing should be [virtual-signal=signal-dot]/(how often it should update)

Final value after parameterizing should be [item=fluid-wagon]>2

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:

Final value after parameterizing should be [item=fluid-wagon]≤1

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
[virtual-signal=signal-yellow] signal generator.
Final values after parameterizing should be [item=fluid-wagon]≤2

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Sends the # of trains worth of [item=parameter-0] fluid that is available at this station, to the global network on the [item=green-wire] wire.

Final values after parameterizing should be [item=fluid-wagon]*1

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
Outputs the train Limit signal. by reading the # of trains worth of fluid available, up to the limit of how many trains can stack at this station.
Important: Should only read the signal on the [item=green-wire] coming from the combinators with the [item=fluid-wagon]&[item=locomotive]'s in them.
Final value after parameterizing should be [virtual-signal=signal-each]*1

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Clock signal reset.
If the # of trains that are either AT or COMING to the station is < the L signal, Increases the station's Priority. 
Resets the priority to 0 if there are enough trains coming to satisfy the call.

Final value after parameterizing should be C<L

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
Limits the # of trains this station can call to the Maximum # of trains that can stack at or behind this station, without clogging the main rail.
Final value after parameterizing should be:[item=fluid-wagon]>[item=locomotive], output [item=locomotive]

entities.name: decider-combinator
entities.player_description:
If the amount of [item=parameter-0] fluid available at this station is ≤ the # of trains that can stack here, Outputs the # of trains to call.
Final value after parameterizing should be [item=fluid-wagon]≤[item=locomotive], output [item=fluid-wagon]

entities.name: arithmetic-combinator
entities.player_description:
[item=fluid-wagon]= # of full trains worth of Fluid available in the buffer.

Calculate by taking quantity of whatever is in the [item=storage-tank], and dividing it by [virtual-signal=signal-K](The capacity of the train to hold that 'parameterized' item)

blueprint.description:
- Set desired Fuel type in the ([virtual-signal=signal-red],[item=parameter-0]) 
 - Place one of these wherever fuel is desired. 
 - Uses an S-R Latch to set high and low fuel 'water' marks.
 - Red light= low or no fuel, & a Train will be called.
 - Cayan= sufficient stock, Fuel requester dissables itself.
 - If updating fuel type, change the the combinator with the red signal in it, the filter on the inserter, & the name of the station next to the [item=substation]to reflect the correct type.

blueprint_book.label: Pre-parameterized Blueprints
blueprint_book.description: If you accidentally change a setting that you didn't mean to, you may need these blueprints to re-parameterize with.

blueprint_book.label: Universal Logistics 1-1 Trains & Stations
blueprint_book.description:
Parameterized Universal logistics 1-1 train system, by Dangwiggums.
Place a blueprint, fill out the parameterized form, connect the colored wire on the power pole to a radar or to the global network of the same color to allow reading of material info.
DO NOT modify the blueprint without making a copy of it first! The parameterization process is... tricky.
